<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3898106>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Details of dorsal pholidosis at mid-body of (A) Cnemaspis heteropholis, male, CES L692, (C) Cnemaspis magnifica sp. nov., holotype, NCBS-BH699; and details of ventral scales at mid-body (B) Cnemaspis heteropholis, male, CES L692, (D) Cnemaspis magnifica sp. nov., holotype, NCBS-BH699. Scale bars 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3898106/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3898108>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Habitat photo of (A) Cnemaspis heteropholis near Gund, Uttar Kannada District, Karnataka, (B) Cnemaspis magnifica sp. nov. near Yadekumari village, Hassan District, Karnataka, India." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3898108/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3898110>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Cnemaspis magnifica sp. nov. (holotype, NCBS-BH699): (A) dorsal view of body, (B) ventral view of body, (C) dorsal view of tail, and (D) ventral view of tail. Scale bars 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3898110/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3898112>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Cnemaspis magnifica sp. nov. (holotype, NCBS-BH699), (A) dorsal view of head, (B) ventral view of head, (C) lateral view of head, (D) view of femoral region showing femoral pores, (E) ventral view of right manus, and (F) ventral view of right pes. Scale bars 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3898112/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3898116>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Cnemaspis magnifica sp. nov. in life: (A) male, holotype, NCBS-BH699, (B) female, paratype, BNHS 2547 and (C) male, paratype, BNHS 2546." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3898116/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3898114>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Type series of Cnemaspis magnifica sp. nov.: (A) from left to right, BNHS 2547, NCBS-BH700, NCBS-BH701, NCBS-BH702, BNHS 2545, BNHS 2546. Scale bar 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3898114/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3898098>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Elevational map of southwestern India showing known localities of Cnemaspis heteropholis (1, type locality, Gund; 2, Castle Rock, 3, Ram Dongar & Verlem, 4, Ulavi) and the type locality of C. magnifica sp. nov. (5, Sakleshpur); and left inset, maximum likelihood phylogeny of South Asian Cnemaspis with major clades collapsed (see Table 1 for list of taxa) and bootstrap support shown above nodes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3898098/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

